# Of or pertaining to the [[zygapophysis]]

the zygapophyseal joint is a same word with the facet joint.

the zygapophyseal or facet joint is formed by the inferior articular process of the thoracic vertebra and the superior articular process of the thoracic vertebra.

the zygapophyseal or facet joint makes flexibility of the spine with the articular cartilage.

when the articular cartilage is degenerated, the inferior articular process of the thoracic vertebra and the superior articular process of the thoracic vertebra will be rubbed each other and cause inflammation or swell.